dated_at":"2018-09-22T15:07:29.982Z","actor":{"username":"albinowax","cleared":true,"url":"/albinowax","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/056/414/9d843d496965d8c0e710de3867a41720c1577dc4_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":3399321,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hi @albinowax - I wanted to follow up on this because we won't be able to get this fixed before your presentation. As discussed outside of HackerOne.com, you are OK to talk about the vulnerability, but please redact the domain you've found it on for the time being. When this is addressed, feel free to disclose that it was us. We've looked into this and determined that this is a problem may be on Acquia's side, which we currently don't have under our control. We'll work with them to get this resolved. Good luck with your presentation and I hope to have an update soon. Good luck and happy hacking!","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2018-09-27T22:04:20.611Z","updated_at":"2018-09-27T22:04:20.611Z","actor":{"username":"jobert","cleared":true,"url":"/jobert","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/ht4b9SmcYNqmpbyCFXd7cxHB/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":true},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":3440033,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Just to confirm, I redacted the vulnerability so there's no mention of HackerOne. You can find the reference towards the end of this post: https://portswigger.net/blog/bypassing-web-cache-poisoni